@abstract:
eNSAID (Environment for NeSy-Agentic Integrated Development) open specification.
Defines the standard for neurosymbolic development environments with Binary Star
human-machine co-orbit architecture.
@end

@canonical-locations:
- SCM files: .machine_readable/ ONLY (.machine_readable/6a2/STATE.a2ml, .machine_readable/6a2/META.a2ml, .machine_readable/6a2/ECOSYSTEM.a2ml)
- Specification sections: spec/ (01 through 09, AsciiDoc)
- License: LICENSE (PMPL-1.0-or-later)
- Security: SECURITY.md
- Contributing: CONTRIBUTING.md
@end

@invariants:
- This is a SPECIFICATION repository, not an implementation
- PanLL is the reference implementation (separate repo)
- "panels" NEVER "panes" in all documents
- RFC 2119 keywords (MUST/SHOULD/MAY) carry normative meaning in spec/ files
- SCM files MUST be in .machine_readable/ ONLY, never in root
- All files MUST have SPDX-License-Identifier headers
@end

@structure:
- README.adoc: Overview and section index
- spec/01-binary-star.adoc: Binary Star architecture
- spec/02-three-panel-model.adoc: Three-panel model (L/N/W)
- spec/03-cognitive-governance.adoc: Cognitive Governance Stack
- spec/04-panel-lifecycle.adoc: Panel lifecycle (5 phases)
- spec/05-panel-contract.adoc: Panel contract format
- spec/06-panel-taxonomy.adoc: Panel taxonomy (cladistic)
- spec/07-contractiles.adoc: Contractile governance
- spec/08-constraint-propagation.adoc: Constraint propagation engine
- spec/09-translation-honesty.adoc: Translation honesty vocabulary
@end

@on-enter:
1. Read this manifest first
2. Read `.machine_readable/6a2/STATE.a2ml` for current project state
3. Read `.machine_readable/6a2/META.a2ml` for architecture decisions
4. Read `.machine_readable/6a2/ECOSYSTEM.a2ml` for ecosystem position
@end
